# Normalize line endings to LF in the repo (the working tree still gets native endings on
# checkout), so a CRLF editor or a Windows clone can't slip \r\n into tracked text. Git
# auto-detects text vs binary; the explicit rules below just pin the known binary assets.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize or try to diff as text.
*.ttf binary
*.glb binary
*.png binary
*.mid binary
*.ply binary
*.wav binary
*.mp4 binary
